3.1:
Each Umamusume has different goals. 
Let's now work to realize these goals!
3.2:
These are the commands that let you 
advance through training.
3.3: Executing one command consumes a turn.
3.4: Let's go with the actual "Training" first!
3.5:
These are the types of training available! 
Each one improves different capabilities.
3.6: Let's see what happens when we choose "Speed"!
3.7:
Now, I want to talk to you about your 
Umamusume's energy when training.
3.8: First, as before, let's choose a training.
3.9: Please pay attention to the "failure rate" here.
3.10:
The less energy you have left, the higher the 
failure rate will be.
3.11:
Failing a training will reduce capabilities and 
mood so be careful…!
3.12: Now, let's get back to it.
3.13: When your Umamusume's energy is low, let her take a rest to recover.
3.15:
Next, choose a skill to learn. 
We'll use the skill points you just earned!
3.16: Let's have her learn this skill for now.
3.18:
And we're all set! 
Let's enter a race!
3.19:
When there is a race that she can run, 
it will show up in the list.
3.20: This time, let's run in this race!
3.21:
In the paddock, you can check the abilities and 
prediction rank of Umamusume running in the race!
3.22:
First of all, let me explain the prediction marks. 
The "◎", "○", "▲", and "△" marks indicate 
ratings in that order, from highest to lowest.
3.23:
The higher her ability and mood, 
the higher the expectations, and the more 
favored an Umamusume is likely to be.
3.24:
Of course, there is no guarantee of victory, but 
broadly speaking the more favored she is, the better 
results you can expect!
3.25:
You can also change the strategy 
of your Umamusume in the paddock.
3.26:
Of course choosing a strategy your 
Umamusume is strong at is a good idea.
3.27:
We're all set now! 
It's time to run the race!!
3.29:
If you have any skill points left, please don't 
forget to use them.
3.30: Well then, that's it for training!
3.31:
Once an Umamusume has been trained, she will be 
evaluated based on certain criteria and then 
registered as a "Hall of Fame Umamusume".
3.32: Good luck in your quest for the highest rank!
3.33:
Once training is complete, your Umamusume 
may acquire a "factor".
3.34:
When selecting an Umamusume as parent, her 
desires and experiences will be passed on 
through their special bond as these "factors"!
3.35: Congratulations on finishing in first place!
3.36:
Your Umamusume deserves lots of 
praise for her hard work!
3.37: After the race there is normally a winning live performance, but since we're in the middle of your introduction, let's skip that.
3.39:
Although it was short in this introduction, the 
actual training period is 3 years.
3.40:
Please cherish the days you spend 
with any Umamusume in your care!
3.41:
The three marks indicate the predictions of experts, 
and the expectations ranking shows the anticipation of fans.

63.1: A lot of things happen every day at the Tracen Academy. Select a <color=#ff9900>training scenario</color> and solve the problems surrounding the school. Conquering these scenarios will help your Umamusume grow!
63.2: Spend 3 years with an Umamusume in the <color=#ff9900>Twinkle Series</color> and work together to make their <color=#ff9900>dreams come true</color>! Every Umamusume has different goals. Guide many different girls to become a great trainer.
63.3: All of the Umamusume have unique personalities. Each Umamusume has different basic abilities, skills, and aptitudes. You can train them as many times as you like, so let's start by <color=#ff9900>raising your favorite Umamusume</color>.
63.4: Inheriting <color=#ff9900>feelings (factors)</color> increases ability and aptitude at the start of training, and your Umamusume will grow through <color=#ff9900>Inheritance Events</color>. Inherited girls won't disappear from the Hall of Fame, so take advantage to raise stronger Umamusume!
63.5: <color=#ff9900>Organize</color> Support Cards to receive corresponding <color=#ff9900>support effects</color> and <color=#ff9900>training events</color> from those characters. Note that you can not use cards of the Umamusume you are training.
63.6: There are <color=#ff9900>types (specialty training)</color> of Support Cards. The effects they exhibit when training together are different.
63.7: When you raise the Friendship Gauge of your Support Card during training and perform your specialty training, <color=#ff9900>Friendship Training</color> will occur. In Friendship Training, your Umamusume will grow bigger than normal!
63.8: Use <color=#ff9900>enhancement items</color> to increase your <color=#ff9900>Awakening Level</color>. Raising your Awakening Level will increase the number of skills you can acquire during training. Reinforcement items can be obtained through training and daily races.
63.9: Use <color=#ff9900>Umamusume pieces</color> to <color=#ff9900>Develop</color> them. This will increase the basic ability of the Umamusume. Also, when they reach 3★ they will receive their <color=#ff9900>signature racewear</color>.
63.10: Use your <color=#ff9900>Support Pt</color> and <color=#ff9900>Money</color> to <color=#ff9900>increase the level</color>. As the level increases, your support effects will increase, giving you an edge in your training. Strengthening items can be obtained through training and daily races.
63.11: Use <color=#ff9900>copies of the same Support Card</color> to <color=#ff9900>Uncap</color>. Uncapping increases the upper level limit and you can further strengthen the Support Card's level.
63.12: Support Cards dupes can be converted into <color=#ff9900>Horseshoes</color>. These valuable items can be exchanged in the store. The first Support Card you acquire will be stored in the Support Card list, subsequent cards will be displayed in the vault and can be converted.
63.13: When you complete training, your Umamusume will be saved in the <color=#ff9900>Hall of Fame</color>. Once there, she can enter the Team Stadium and various races, can be inherited from in training, or transferred, upon which she is irrevocably lost.
63.14: Umamusume pieces can be converted into <color=#ff9900>clovers</color>. Clovers are valuable and can be exchanged for items in the store. Be careful when converting pieces, as they can be used to release the Umamusume you are training and to develop new talents.
63.16: Meeting new Umamusume and increasing their <color=#ff9900>Bond Level</color> allows you to progress through <color=#ff9900>their personal stories</color>. Rewards are gained for progressing through the stories.
63.17: Form a <color=#ff9900>team</color> of Hall of Fame Umamusume and compete against teams from all over the country in the <color=#ff9900>Team Stadium</color>. Your team's <color=#ff9900>CLASS</color> will increase according to its success, and each week you will earn rewards according to the CLASS you belong to.
63.18: A <color=#ff9900>high score</color> will be recorded for outstanding race results. Each week, the CLASS to which you belong will change based on your high score.
63.19: In the Team Stadium, five races with different <color=#ff9900>conditions</color> are held at a time. The higher your CLASS, the more people you can run in each race, up to a maximum of 15 Umamusume. Form the strongest team you can and challenge the Team Stadium!
63.20: Form your own <color=#ff9900>team</color> of <color=#ff9900>Hall of Famers</color>. For each of the five races with different conditions, select the Umamusume with the best aptitude. The <color=#ff9900>ace</color> Umamusume will get <color=#ff9900>1.1 times</color> the score.
63.21: The more strong Umamusume you have in your team, the higher your <color=#ff9900>team rating</color> will be and the higher your <color=#ff9900>team rank</color> will be. The higher your team rank, the more rewards you can earn.
63.22: In the Team Stadium, you will play against <color=#ff9900>opponents with similar team ratings</color>. The higher your team rating, the higher your score will be. Form a strong team and conquer the Team Stadium!
63.23: Challenge the Legend Race with your saved Umamusume. The higher you finish, the more rewards you get. Tickets required for participation are replenished at 05:00 during the event period and when the LEGEND Umamusume is switched.
63.24: Take on the Daily Race with your Hall of Fame Umamusume. You can earn various rewards depending on the races you challenge. Each day, you will receive up to the <color=#ff9900>maximum number of tickets</color>.
63.25: In Practice, you can freely hold races under <color=#ff9900>any conditions you want</color>. In addition to the Hall of Fame Umamusume you have bred, you can also run races with <color=#ff9900>other trainers' Umamusume</color>. You can hold practice with up to 18 Umamusume at once!
63.26: If you see any Umamusume you like in the Team Stadium or room match, you can register her as your <color=#ff9900>Training Partner</color> so that you can run races with her. The representative Umamusume of the friends you are following will also be able to run in the race.
63.27: You can <color=#ff9900>share</color> your favorite <color=#ff9900>Hall of Fame Umamusume</color> with your Circle and SNS. Actively register your Practice Partners from Circle members and friends to enhance your practice!
63.30: Join a <color=#ff9900>Circle</color> with other trainers from around the country. You can interact with other members and help each other with training.
63.31: Members can give each other a <color=#ff9900>variety of items</color>. You can also rent each other's <color=#ff9900>representative Umamusume</color> for inheritance at a discount.
63.32: <size=26>You can watch live performances of <color=#ff9900>songs</color> you have acquired. Select main and back dancers from obtained Umamusume and acquired costumes to watch the live with your favorite combination. Songs marked with <color=#ff9900>"Singing"</color>, are voiced by the selected Umamusume. Songs can be acquired through the main story and training.</size>
63.33: You can check and set your trainer information. On your <color=#ff9900>birthday</color>, you will receive a congratulatory comment from Umamusume on the home screen, and changing your <color=#ff9900>gender</color> will change some scenarios. (Gender can be changed at any time)
63.34: You can set up a <color=#ff9900>representative Umamusume</color> and <color=#ff9900>Support Card</color> to help your followers in their training. You will earn <color=#ff9900>Friend Pt the next day</color> depending on the number of times you do this. (This will be given as a gift)
63.35: You can earn titles through <color=#ff9900>title missions</color> and <color=#ff9900>events</color>. You can change the title you have earned at any time.
63.36: Help the Director reach her dream! You can earn <color=#ff9900>trophies and rewards</color> when you win graded races during training, or Legend Races. In addition, you can earn rewards by completing missions to collect the specified number of trophies.
63.37: You can select the representative Umamusume and Support Card of the friends you <color=#ff9900>follow</color> from each list in training. You also earn more Friend Pt by helping a <color=#ff9900>mutual follower</color> to train. If you don't have many followers, try looking in the <color=#ff9900>recommendations</color>.
63.38: Collect records related to Umamusume to raise your <color=#ff9900>Index Level</color>. You'll accumulate Index Exp based on the evaluation points you've earned through training and the stories you've viewed, and you'll earn rewards as your Index Level increases.
63.39: Take aim and catch Umamusume plushies (Paka-Puchi)! You have <color=#ff9900>3 attempts</color> to catch at least one. Your Umamusume might even gain a <color=#ff9900>new hint</color>!?
63.40: Congratulations on your <color=#ff9900>CLASS 2</color> promotion! The <color=#ff9900>second slot</color> for team formation has been released. The second slot for team formation has been released, allowing you to organize more Umamusume for the Hall of Fame.
63.41: Congratulations on your <color=#ff9900>CLASS 3</color> promotion! The <color=#ff9900>third slot</color> for team formation has been released, allowing you to organize more Hall of Fame Umamusume.
63.42: The aim of the training is to achieve good results in the <color=#ff9900>target races</color> set for each Umamusume. In order to achieve good results in races, you need to <color=#ff9900>develop your basic abilities</color> through <color=#ff9900>training</color>!
63.43: By acquiring <color=#ff9900>skills</color>, you can gain a <color=#ff9900>variety of effects</color> in <color=#ff9900>races</color>. The Skill Points needed to acquire skills are mainly obtained through races, but can also be obtained through some events.
63.44: If your Umamusume's <color=#ff9900>energy or mood is low</color> she will not be able to perform at her best in training or races. <color=#ff9900>Resting</color> restores energy, and <color=#ff9900>going out</color> boosts mood. Always pay attention to her condition!
63.45: During training, you may acquire <color=#ff9900>conditions</color> that have a negative effect on your Umamusume's training and physical condition. The <color=#ff9900>Infirmary</color> can eliminate such conditions, so think about making use of it quickly.
63.46: You can execute various commands while training your Umamusume! Use each command in a well-balanced manner to make your Umamusume into a great Umamusume!
63.47: From the latter half of June in Junior class, you can start <color=#ff9900>racing</color>. Train your Umamusume well and aim for <color=#ff9900>first place</color>! In races, you earn <color=#ff9900>Skill Points</color> to acquire skills and <color=#ff9900>Fans</color> to run in big races, based on your finishing position. You'll also earn random items based on your position and margin.
63.48: Umamusume make their first appearance on the racing stage in their <color=#ff9900>make debut</color>. If they finish first, they can run in various races. If they don't, you'll have to try to win one of the <color=#ff9900>Maiden Races</color> available!
63.49: <color=#ff9900>Basic abilities</color> such as speed and stamina, gained through training, are linked to <color=#ff9900>the various abilities displayed during races</color>. Which you need varies greatly with <color=#ff9900>distance</color> and <color=#ff9900>running strategy</color>, so <color=#ff9900>create a training menu that suits her</color>!
63.50: The <color=#ff9900>surface and distance</color> where the races take place differ. Your Umamusume suits different tracks depending on her <color=#ff9900>surface and distance aptitudes</color>. Aim for races that are <color=#ff9900>marked with a ★</color> in the list, and go for the win!
63.51: The races are divided into five grades: <color=#ff9900>Pre-Open, Open, G3, G2, and G1</color>. Let's start with the <color=#ff9900>Pre-Open, Open</color> to win the highest G1 race in the Twinkle Series!
63.52: You can grow your Umamusume's <color=#ff9900>basic abilities</color> by spending <color=#ff9900>energy</color> to <color=#ff9900>train</color> her. In addition to <color=#ff9900>recovering</color> energy, more <color=#ff9900>Skill Points</color> can be gained from the Wit training than other training.
63.53: Training with Umamusume organized as a <color=#ff9900>Support Card</color> will increase your <color=#ff9900>training efficiency and bond gauge</color>. When the bond gauge is full, <color=#ff9900>Friendship Training</color> can occur. You may <color=#ff9900>gain various benefits</color> if certain others watch you train as well.
63.54: When a Support Card Umamusume has a <color=#ff9900>! mark</color> on her, grab your chance to <color=#ff9900>increase Hint Level of one of this partner's skills</color> upon successfully completing the training session. This will confer a <color=#ff9900>discount on the Skill Pt needed to acquire the skill</color>.
63.55: If you train your Umamusume when her <color=#ff9900>energy is low</color>, she may <color=#ff9900>fail the training</color> and her ability may not improve. There are <color=#ff9900>various disadvantages</color> to failing a training session, so always keep an eye on her <color=#ff9900>energy and failure rate</color>!
63.56: By spending <color=#ff9900>Skill Points</color>, you can acquire <color=#ff9900>skills</color> that activate during races. There are various conditions to activate skills, such as the <color=#ff9900>race distance and running strategy</color>, so try to <color=#ff9900>acquire skills that match her aptitudes</color>.
63.57: The <color=#ff9900>Hint Level</color> of a skill may be increased by the result of a <color=#ff9900>Support Card or Umamusume Event</color>. The skill Pt you <color=#ff9900>consume will be discounted</color> depending on the Hint Level, so organize Support Cards that have the skills you want to acquire to get the best deals.
63.58: <size=26>There are three main types of skills. <color=#ff9900>Unique skills</color> are special skills that your Umamusume starts with. <color=#ff9900>Rare skills</color> are powerful skills found in special situations. <color=#ff9900>Normal Skills</color> are skills found in various situations. There are also skills that can only be acquired by <color=#ff9900>inheriting certain factors</color>.</size>
63.59: If you raise the level of your Support Card to a certain level, you will get a <color=#ff9900>support bonus that will increase your score in the Team Stadium</color>. Let's raise the lvl of many Support Cards!
63.62: During the event period, <color=#ff9900>train your Umamusume</color>and earn <color=#ff9900>Event Points</color>. By collecting Event Points, you can earn various<color=#ff9900>rewards</color>.
63.63: Collecting Event Points will allow you to advance through the <color=#ff9900>event-only story</color>. By advancing the story and clearing event missions, you can earn <color=#ff9900>event limited Support Cards, rainbow fragments, and titles</color>.
63.64: At the end of training, any <color=#ff9900>event bonus Umamusume or Support Cards</color> will confer a <color=#ff9900>bonus to the event points gained</color>.
63.65: You can get <color=#ff9900>Event Pt and Roulette Coins</color> by completing event missions. You can also earn Roulette Coins from the <color=#ff9900>daily missions</color>.
63.66: You can play <color=#ff9900>roulette derby</color> using <color=#ff9900>roulette coins</color> If you <color=#ff9900>achieve bingo</color>, you can get <color=#ff9900>event limited Support Cards and gold fragments</color>.
63.67: During the event period, you can earn <color=#ff9900>roulette coins</color> by <color=#ff9900>training Umamusume</color> and completing <color=#ff9900>event missions</color>. Collect <color=#ff9900>roulette coins</color>to spin the <color=#ff9900>roulette derby</color> wheel.
63.68: You can get <color=#ff9900>roulette rewards</color> according to your finishing order in the roulette derby. When you get a roulette reward you've never gotten before, it's your chance to BINGO!
63.69: Cells will be filled according to roulette rewards earned. When 3 consecutive squares are filled (on any axis), <color=#ff9900>a line is completed</color>, and you will receive a <color=#ff9900>BINGO reward</color> based on number of lines. Complete <color=#ff9900>8 lines of BINGO</color>to exchange your first 3 sheets.
63.70: Run in the <color=#ff9900>Aoharu Hai</color>, held the turn after June and December end, and aim for victory with your team. Winning will increase your <color=#ff9900>team ranking</color>, and your <color=#ff9900>Umamusume and team members will grow</color>. Train a strong Umamusume to <color=#ff9900>win lots of Aoharu Hai</color>!
63.71: Put together a team to win the Aoharu Hai! With races in each category, the winner will be the one with <color=#ff9900>more wins</color> out of five. <color=#ff9900>Winning raises your team ranking</color>, more so the higher your opponent's ranking.
63.72: By using the pieces you have collected, you can <color=#ff9900>release</color> your breeding Umamusume. Once released, you will be able to take charge of them in training.
63.73: Register 3 Umamusume to <color=#ff9900>match</color> and battle with <color=#ff9900>other trainers</color> in real time! Raise strong Umamusume and aim for glory!
63.74: There are two leagues, the <color=#ff9900>Open League</color> and the <color=#ff9900>Graded League</color>, and you can select the one that suits you best Depending on the league, the upper limit of the <color=#ff9900>breeding rank</color> of the Hall of Fame Umamusume you can register to run in the race will differ.
63.75: <color=#ff9900>Room Match</color> allows you to race against other trainers with your Hall of Fame Umamusume <color=#ff9900>Host</color>: Set your own conditions for the race <color=#ff9900>Join</color>: Join another trainer's race. <color=#ff9900>Watch</color>: Enter an ID to watch the race.
63.76: The race held will be G1. There are two modes. <color=#ff9900>Simple Mode</color> allows you to hold a race right away. <color=#ff9900>Detailed mode</color> allows you to select weather, participation conditions, etc. first. Up to <color=#ff9900>3 Umamusume per person</color> can be entered.
63.77: <color=#ff9900>The league is made up of three rounds</color>. Starting from Round 2, you will be divided into Group A and Group B, and the places you advance to will depend on your performance in each round and group. Let's move on to the final round and win the <color=#ff9900>winner</color>!
63.78: Recruit participants for your races from the participation list. Trainers close to you can also be recruited using the <color=#ff9900>Circle and SNS Sharing functions</color>. For future reference, <color=#ff9900>you can save your favorite races</color>. Have a go organizing a race with your friends!
63.80: In Special Transfers, you can <color=#ff9901>transfer your trained Umamusume to another trainer's team for rewards</color>. Be aware that once you transfer someone, she will be gone and you will not be able to get her back.
63.81: Each team has its own expectations. These not only come with <color=#ff9901>different rewards</color>, but <color=#ff9901>the higher the expectations, the more luxurious the rewards</color> for transferring your Umamusume to them.
63.82: Teams with high expectations will reward a piece of the transferred <color=#ff9901>Hall of Fame Umamusume</color> as a thank you gift.
63.83: If you train at a training location where a team member has a special icon, "<color=#ff9900>Aoharu Special Training</color>" will occur, and <color=#ff9900>that team member's basic abilities will increase</color>. Let's use the Aoharu Training to grow our team so we can win the Aoharu Hai!
63.84: Furthermore, a Special Training session <color=#ff9900>with 2 or more</color> team members, will <color=#ff9900>boost your Umamusume's training efficiency</color> as well. <color=#ff9900>Basic abilities and skill points gained</color> will also increase <color=#ff9900>the more team members</color> participate.
63.86: Team members you have had many Special Trainings with can have an <color=#ff9900>Aoharu Spirit Explosion</color> once. Their <color=#ff9900>basic abilities will increase greatly</color> and <color=#ff9900>your Umamusume will also grow and get Skill Hints</color> The key to success is <color=#ff9900>generating many Aoharu Spirit Explosions</color>!
63.87: You can check the items you currently have. You can also use consumable items. Some items can be converted to Money. <color=#ff9900>Converting items cannot be undone</color>, so be careful.
63.88: As team members grow, <color=#ff9900>team strength</color> will increase and you will receive gifts from Tazuna. Also, each member's <color=#ff9900>Training Level will increase</color> with their basic ability. <color=#ff9900>The strength of your team will lead to the growth of your Umamusume</color> , so be proactive in training your team!
63.89: The <color=#ff9900>team title</color> is an <color=#ff9900>evaluation of your overall</color> team strength and team ranking. <color=#ff9900>The better the team title you have, the more your Umamusume will grow in the ending</color> Let's win Aoharu Hai and get the strongest team title!
63.90: Using <color=#ff9900>Event Boost</color> you can spend twice the TP at the start of training to gain double the <color=#ff9900>Event Pt</color> and <color=#ff9900>Roulette coins</color> at the end.
63.91: You can <color=#ff9900>Uncap</color> Support Cards by using <color=#ff9900>duplicates of the same card</color>. The level limit will be increased. SR and SSR Support Cards can also be uncapped by using <color=#ff9900>Release Crystals</color>.
63.92: When you end training in <color=#ff9900>Showtime Mode</color>, your <color=#ff9900>SHOW Gauge</color> will rise according to your progress and the difficulty level. You will receive <color=#ff9900>additional rewards</color> according to the number of times you've filled your SHOW Gauge to MAX.
63.93: In Showtime Mode, the <color=#ff9900>opponent Umamusume</color> will become stronger in training races. When you see the <color=#ff9900>good ending of your Umamusume </color> at the chosen difficulty level, the next level will be unlocked and can be challenged from next training.
63.94: You can earn more points by training Umamusume <color=#ff9900>according to their aptitude</color> and by achieving the specified <color=#ff9900>Score Bonus</color> conditions.
63.95: In the <color=#ff9900>Trainer Proficiency Exam</color>, you can check the <color=#ff9900>usage rate of Support Cards</color> for each test in the ranking!
63.96: A scenario without individual goals, <color=#ff9900>instead chasing "Result Points"</color>. Acquire fixed amounts from each of the 3 years! You can freely enter any races during training, and obtained Pts depend on the race's grade and finishing position!
63.97: <color=#ff9900>Once all training objectives are complete</color>, you can challenge the <color=#ff9900>Twinkle Star Climax</color>! Emerge victorious over the 3-race battle to claim your place as "Twinkle Top Star"!
63.98: When entering races, you will <color=#ff9900>obtain Shop Coins</color>! Shop Coins can be traded for training items in the special shop. Training items can increase stats, recover energy, boost training growths, and have <color=#ff9900>various other effects that are sure to help your training</color>!
63.99: <color=#ff9900>After each second half of December</color>, when changing years, <color=#ff9900>the most outstanding Umamusume is recognized</color>. Do well in races while deepening bonds with your supporters to increase your fans! When chosen, your Umamusume's unique skill will level up, in addition to other improvements!
63.100: Sometimes Rivals will enter races. When <color=#ff9900>entering and winning those races</color> your <color=#ff9900>Umamusume's stats will grow</color>, and she can <color=#ff9900>obtain Skill Hints</color>. Grow your Umamusume more by having them fight these tough opponents!
63.101: In the Twinkle Star Climax, <color=#ff9900>you gain Result Pt based on your finishing position</color>, and the <color=#ff9900>Umamusume with the most Pts over 3 races is the winner</color>. Aim for the top with your carefully trained Umamusume!
63.102: In Practice, you can freely hold races under <color=#ff9900>any conditions you want</color>. In addition to the Hall of Fame Umamusume you have bred, you can also run races with <color=#ff9900>other trainers' Umamusume</color>. You can hold practice with up to 18 Umamusume at once!
63.103: If you see any Umamusume you like in the Team Stadium or room match, you can register her as your <color=#ff9900>Training Partner</color> so that you can run races with her. The representative Umamusume of the friends you are following will also be able to run in the race.
63.104: You can <color=#ff9900>share</color> your favorite <color=#ff9900>Hall of Fame Umamusume</color> with your Circle and SNS. Actively register your Practice Partners from Circle members and friends to enhance your practice!
63.105: Save Umas in <color=#ff9900>My Entrants</color> to <color=#ff9900>select them easily</color> during registration! You can also save them from the results screen. Removing Training Partners, will remove them from My Entrants as well, so be careful!
63.106: Save Umas in <color=#ff9900>My Entrants</color> to <color=#ff9900>select them easily</color> during registration! You can also save them from the results screen. Removing Training Partners, will remove them from My Entrants as well, so be careful!
63.107: You can view the <color=#ff9900>Top 100 highest scorers</color> in the ranking! The <color=#ff9900>Top 30 Umamusume</color> can be <color=#ff9900>rented without limit</color> in the relevant scenario.
63.108: <color=#ff9900>Trial Coins</color> are earned for exams, and extra can be earned through <color=#ff9900>Score Bonuses</color>, <color=#ff9900>Exam Grades</color>, and <color=#ff9900>Missions</color>.
63.109: You can increase the <color=#ff9900>Hint Level</color> of your Umamusume's skills by using <color=#ff9900>upgrade items</color>. When doing so, she will start training with her <color=#ff9900>Hint Level already raised</color> for those skills.
63.110: Race in the Carnival to gain <color=#ff9900>Carnival Pts</color>. Points are awarded for skill uses and finishing position.
63.111: As you complete <color=#ff9900>Carnival Races</color>, your <color=#ff9900>Challenge Gauge</color> will fill. When full, you can enter a <color=#ff9900>Challenge Race</color>. Challenge Races come in <color=#ff9900>VERY HARD and EXTREME</color> difficulties.
63.112: Your Umamusume will gain the <color=#ff9900>Carnival Factor</color> when finishing top 5 in an event race. When an Umamusume inherits this factor, she will gain <color=#ff9900>bonus stats and a chance to max mood</color> in the event races.
63.113: When an Umamusume with the <color=#ff9900>Carnival Bonus Skill</color> finishes top 5 in an event race, the factor will <color=#ff9900>Level up</color>. The <color=#ff9900>stat bonus and max mood chance will increase</color> with skill level.
63.114: The <color=#ff9900>Carnival pts</color> obtained in Racing Carnival races can be <color=#ff9900>traded for items</color> in the shop!
63.115: Challenge the daily Legend races! Pieces of the challenged Legend Umamusume can be acquired. Tickets will <color=#ff9900>refill to max</color> every day.
63.116: Create your own <color=#ff9900>Trainer Card</color>, and share it as an image on social media. Show your info along with Umamusume, support and <color=#ff9900>customizable graphics</color>.
63.117: <color=#ff9900>Factors</color> for your representative Umamusume can also be <color=#ff9900>shared on social media</color>. Show off your glorious Umamusume on your card!
63.118: The <color=#ff9900>Snapshot function</color> allows you to take photos of <color=#ff9900>Races, Lives, and Stories</color>. Snapshots can be processed and edited in a few ways to add your own flair.
63.119: Saved snapshots are stored in the <color=#ff9900>Photo Library</color> and accessible at any time. They can also be used on your <color=#ff9900>Trainer or Circle Cards</color>.
63.120: When entering races, you will <color=#ff9900>obtain Shop Coins</color>! Shop Coins can be traded for training items in the special shop. Training items can increase stats, recover energy, boost training growths, and have <color=#ff9900>various other effects that are sure to help your training</color>!
63.121: For your first training <color=#ff9900>we recommend you play the URA Finals scenario</color> to get to know the Umamusume better! Many things happen on the path you both take towards her unique goals. Aim to win on the big, dream-like stage of the URA Finals!
63.122: Each scenario <color=#ff9900>has many exclusive events!</color> We hope you will enjoy discovering new aspects of the Umamusume through their daily life and their expressions as they go through the seasons!
63.123: <color=#ff9900>Everyone's Top Umadol Project</color> is an event where rewards are gained for obtaining fans through training. Personal rewards are obtained based on total fans gained in training mode.
63.124: When finishing training in <color=#ff9900>Golshi-chan Mode</color> you will gain rewards based on progress. In Golshi-chan mode <color=#ff9900>opponents in races</color> will be stronger.
63.125: Overall rewards are based on <color=#ff9900>total fans gained by all trainers in the event</color>. The more fans, the more luxurious the rewards.
63.126: <color=#ff9900>Room Match</color> allows you to race against other trainers with your Hall of Fame Umamusume <color=#ff9900>Host</color>: Set your own conditions for the race <color=#ff9900>Join</color>: Join another trainer's race. <color=#ff9900>Watch</color>: Enter an ID to watch the race.
63.127: The race held will be G1. There are two modes. <color=#ff9900>Simple Mode</color> allows you to hold a race right away. <color=#ff9900>Detailed mode</color> allows you to select weather, participation conditions, etc. first. Up to <color=#ff9900>3 Umamusume per person</color> can be entered.
63.128: Recruit participants for your races from the participation list. Trainers close to you can also be recruited using the <color=#ff9900>Circle and SNS Sharing functions</color>. For future reference, <color=#ff9900>you can save your favorite races</color>. Have a go organizing a race with your friends!
63.129: Save Umamusume in <color=#ff9900>My Entrants</color> to <color=#ff9900>select them easily</color> during registration! You can also save them from the results screen.
63.130: Save Umamusume in <color=#ff9900>My Entrants</color> to <color=#ff9900>select them easily</color> during registration! You can also save them from the results screen.
63.131: Dress your Umamusume in your favorite outfits! Changing an Umamusume's outfit will change it for <color=#ff9900>all of her Hall of Fame versions</color>. Note that in some situations the outfit won't display.
63.132: You can select <color=#ff9900>Double TP Usage</color> at the start of training to <color=#ff9900>double SHOW gauge fill rate</color> at the end.
63.133: After 4 Promotional Lives, the <color=#ff9900>Grand Live</color> is held! Keeping things fresh and <color=#ff9900>learning various tracks</color> for each Live will greatly benefit your Umamusume!
63.134: Through training, <color=#ff9900>5 different Performances</color> can be earned! Which ones go with which training changes every turn.
63.135: The Performances earned increase with the <color=#ff9900>training's level</color> and the <color=#ff9900>amount of Umamusume participating</color>. Friendship training will also provide 2 Performances!
63.136: The Performances earned can be spend on <color=#ff9900>Lessons</color> to gain <color=#ff9900>Tracks or Live Techniques</color>. Both of these are highly useful to the <color=#ff9900>development of your Umamusume</color>.
63.137: Performances can be spent on <color=#ff9900>Lessons</color> to gain <color=#ff9900>Tracks or Live Techniques</color>! Learning these will provide an immediate <color=#ff9900>Talent Bonus</color>, and Tracks will additionally provide a <color=#ff9900>Live Bonus</color> which will be active from the next Live until the end of training.
63.138: When lacking the Performances for a Lesson, it can be <color=#ff9900>reserved</color>. Doing so will display the <color=#ff9900>Performances needed</color> to learn it in the Training screens.
63.139: Each Track learned will increase the <color=#ff9900>Live Anticipation</color>. Maxing this gauge will ensure the live's <color=#ff9900>Great Success</color>. Anticipation will reset every live, so prepare new Tracks for each live!
63.140: At a <color=#ff9900>Live</color>, the <color=#ff9900>songs learnt will be played</color>. With a specific number of new Tracks, the <color=#ff9900>live will be a Great Success</color>. Umamusume will <color=#ff9900>grow more</color> when the live is a Great Sucess, so aim for this using the Anticipation gauge as reference.
63.141: When new Tracks are played at a Live, their <color=#ff9900>Live Bonus</color> will be active from the next turn. Similar bonuses will <color=#ff9900>stack</color>.
63.142: In <color=#ff9901>Special Transfer StarHorse4 Edition</color> you can transfer your trained Umamusume to another team to receive rewards. Be careful, the transfer is permanent, and you can't just call those girls back!
63.143: The <color=#ff9901>expectations</color> of the receiving teams differ, and based on that and the Umamusume you sent the rewards can change. <color=#ff9901>The trainer you're transferring to</color> seems to have a request of <color=#ff9901>☆4 difficulty</color>!
63.144: In ☆3 difficulty requests, you will receive <color=#ff9901>pieces of the Umamusume you sent</color>. Moreover, from this difficulty onwards you can get <color=#ff9901>Star Fruits</color> exclusive to this <color=#ff9901>StarHorse4 Edition</color>.
63.145: Take on Scout Races with a team of 7. The Team captain will be one of your trained Umamusume. The others can be selected through <color=#ff9900>scouting</color>. Build the strongest team through continuous <color=#ff9900>racing and scouting</color>!
63.146: You can obtain up to 5 <color=#ff9900>Scout Race Tickets</color> every day at 12. Daily missions and items can also grant you some. <color=#ff9900>Every 3 races</color>, the <color=#ff9900>race details</color> will change. You can check this from the Race Schedule.
63.147: Entering Scout Races will grant <color=#ff9900>Scout Pt</color>. The amount will vary based on race result, opponent team rank, and any bonuses. Aim to win a variety of different races!
63.148: During <color=#ff9900>Scout Time</color>, you can <color=#ff9900>scout</color> the opponent's Umamusume and swap around your own team. The <color=#ff9900>Scout Pt</color> needed to scout depend on the target Umamusume's rank.
63.149: Strengthen your team and <color=#ff9900>increase team rank</color> to receive rewards. In addition, clear <color=#ff9900>limited missions</color> to gain more rewards!
63.150: When you <color=#ff9900>win</color> a <color=#ff9900>Scout Race</color>, the team captain and members are registered in the <color=#ff9900>Roster</color>, and you will get a bonus to the entire team's stats and your Scout Pt. Further, by drafting specific combinations of Umamusume in your team you can obtain <color=#ff9900>Team Skills</color> upon victory.
63.151: The <color=#ff9900>Event Boost</color> lets you use double the TP at the start of training to double the amount of <color=#ff9900>Trial Coin</color> received at the end.
63.152: You can fill the <color=#ff9900>Stroll Gauge</color> by playing <color=#ff9900>various parts of the game</color> or through the <color=#ff9900>stroll login bonus</color>. Once the gauge is at <color=#ff9900>MAX</color>, you can <color=#ff9900>take a stroll</color> with one of your Umamusume. ※The gauge will fill from play after using your login bonus.
63.153: With the Photo Studio you can take <color=#ff9900>photos at training, outings</color>, and various other settings.
63.154: After selecting an Umamusume to photograph, you can set up the <color=#ff9900>seasons, locations, and so on</color>. For <color=#ff9900>training photos</color> partners can also be selected.
63.155: During shooting the action can be <color=#ff9900>paused or looped</color>. Find the perfect timing to snap your favourite shots! Photos can also be <color=#ff9900>edited with filters and the like</color>.
63.156: Going for a stroll increases your <color=#ff9900>Stroll Partner's Friendship</color>. Different <color=#ff9900>destinations</color> will play unique animations and provide different <color=#ff9900>rewards</color>. During the campaign you can rewatch any animations you've seen by long-clicking an Umamusume.
63.157: On the KIRARI MAGIC SHOW campaign page you can check not only campaign info but from 21 December you can join in on the TOKYO MEGA ILLUMI collab event, as well as find a gift hiding in the <color=#ff9900>present box once a day</color>.
63.158:
4.5th Anniversary Challenge Event: The Road to 100,000,000 Subscribers on Umatube!
Train Umamusume to gain subscribers for the Umatube Channel and unlock <color=#ff9900>event rewards</color> as your <color=#ff9900>subscriber count grows</color>.
63.159: <color=#ff9900>Happy Meek</color> will appear in training! Work together with her and aim to enter the URA Finals!
63.160: Training with her can trigger a <color=#ff9900>Duel</color> around a specific stat or energy level! The higher this chosen Duel Subject is, the easier it will be to win the Duel, so train well!
63.161: Should you manage to win a certain number of Duels, a <color=#ff9900>stronger Happy Meek</color> will appear in the URA Finals! Train your Umamusume to take victory on the Finals stage!
63.162: After a team member has had a Spirit Explosion, they can have one further <color=#ff9900>EX Spirit Explosion</color>! This will <color=#ff9900>grant them even more stats, as will your Umamusume, who will additionally receive a special skill hint</color>! EX Spirit Explosions add even more fire to your training!
63.163: Under <color=#ff9900>certain conditions</color>, you can face a <color=#ff9900>Powerhouse Team</color> in the Aoharu Hai! When winning against this team your Umamusume will grow considerably! <color=#ff9900>Something may happen in the finals</color> too…!?
63.164: You can also earn <color=#ff9900>community-wide rewards</color> based on the <color=#ff9900>total subscriber count collected by everyone</color>.
63.165: With the <color=#ff9900>ornaments gathered by all trainers</color> we can make the MEGA TREE glitter as it should. Watch the <color=#ff9900>tree change</color> on the event homepage and help claim the extravagant global event rewards by collecting tons of ornaments!
63.166: Reach for your Umamusume's dreams over 3 years with the aid of the three goddesses! <color=#ff9900>Clear all goals to enter the special Grand Masters race!</color> Hold your own against the goddesses and aim for victory!
63.167: The goddesses will bestow <color=#ff9900>Knowledge Shards</color> upon you when training, resting, going out, or racing! These shards will grant <color=#ff9900>increased stat gains</color> and other useful effects. <color=#ff9900>And friendship training grants 2 shards at once!?</color>
63.168: Every 2 <color=#ff9900>Knowledge Shards</color> will also grant a <color=#ff9900>Knowledge Crystal</color>! These also bestow effects to improve your training. <color=#ff9900>Crystals inherit effects from their shards</color>, so pile them up and strengthen your Umamusume!
63.169: Shards and Crystals collected show in the Knowledge Tree. Reach the end to obtain <color=#ff9900>Goddess's Wisdom</color>! Use this wisdom whenever you wish to <color=#ff9900>power up various actions for 1 turn</color>! The effects vary per goddess, so check the details in the tree.
63.170: Before you can enter the Grand Masters, you will face a <color=#ff9900>special race at the end of each year</color>! Seize victory in all of them with your Umamusume and the power of the goddesses!
63.171: The Grand Masters is 1 special race, facing the ultimate rivals in the <color=#ff9900>three goddesses</color> themselves! <color=#ff9900>Darley Arabian, Godolphin Barb, and Byerley Turk</color> await! Challenge them with your well-trained Umamusume and seize victory!
63.172: This event is divided in a <color=#ff9901>Main Stage</color> and an <color=#ff9901>Extra Stage</color>. In the Main Stage you take on races with a team of three. Based on how you do, your <color=#ff9901>League Score</color> will increase, and based on this score, your <color=#ff9901>League Rank</color> increases, granting various rewards!
63.176: Fill the research gauge by <color=#ff9900>playing various content</color>. When the gauge is filled at least once, return to the event page to receive an amount of <color=#ff9900>research rewards</color> equal to gauge fills.
63.177: <color=#ff9900>The login bloom bonus</color>, <color=#ff9900>completing training</color>, and <color=#ff9900>entering stadium </color> will fill your <color=#ff9900>bloom gauge</color>. When the gauge is at <color=#ff9900>MAX</color> you can <color=#ff9900>move 1 cell further</color> on the main event page. ※ The gauge will fill from play after using your bloom bonus.
63.178: Upon moving cells, their <color=#ff9900>local episodes</color> are unlocked, and their <color=#ff9900>reward</color> acquired. On 4/2 & 4/3 at 12:00 a <color=#ff9900>new area</color> will unlock, allowing you to move into new cells. ※ The bloom gauge won't fill if there are no new cells to move to.
63.179: During training, fulfilling the conditions for the Rare Skills unlocked by awakening an Umamusume allows you to upgrade them to powerful <color=#ff9900>Evolved Skills</color> unique to each Umamusume at the end of training.
63.180: By spending <color=#ff9900>Skill Points</color>, you can acquire <color=#ff9900>skills</color> that activate during races. There are various conditions to activate skills, such as the <color=#ff9900>race distance and running strategy</color>, so try to <color=#ff9900>acquire skills that match her aptitudes</color>.
63.181: The <color=#ff9900>Hint Level</color> of a skill may be increased by the result of a <color=#ff9900>Support Card or Umamusume Event</color>. The skill Pt you <color=#ff9900>consume will be discounted</color> depending on the Hint Level, so organize Support Cards that have the skills you want to acquire to get the best deals.
63.182: <size=26>There are three main types of skills. <color=#ff9900>Unique skills</color> are special skills that your Umamusume starts with. <color=#ff9900>Rare skills</color> are powerful skills found in special situations. <color=#ff9900>Normal Skills</color> are skills found in various situations. There are also skills that can only be acquired by <color=#ff9900>inheriting certain factors</color>.</size>
63.184: The <color=#ff9900>Factor Research Reports</color> obtained as rewards for research allow you to increase the <color=#ff9900>★</color> of an Umamusume's <color=#ff9900>factor</color>. ※ Reports apply to most but not all factors. ※ Reports don't carry over to next event.
63.185: Using the <color=#ff9900>Event Boost</color>, twice the TP will be used at the start of training to double the <color=#ff9900>Research Gauge's fill rate</color>.
63.186: Each area's final cell is the <color=#ff9900>destination</color>. Reaching it unlocks a <color=#ff9900>special video</color>. Videos are available from 4/1～4/3 at 19:00 and 4/4 at 12:00.
63.187: For a time you can <color=#ff9900>cheer for an Umamusume by hitting the "Neighce!" button</color>! Doing so grants you some <color=#ff9900>neighce rewards</color> and can be done once per block (A-B).
63.188: The Extra Stage has opened! You can watch the main race for the A and B blocks and each race of your own team. Watching races grants rewards too!
63.189: Circles can create their own original <color=#ff9901>Circle Cards</color> and share them as images on <color=#ff9901>social media</color>. These are customizable cards showing the Circle's details and other info.
63.190: At <color=#ff9900>12am every day</color> you receive <color=#ff9900>5 League Tickets</color>, each of which grants entry to <color=#ff9900>5 races</color>. Each race features 5 teams, with the weather and going randomized every race. No other race conditions will change.
63.191: With each entered race, your <color=#ff9900>Hero Gauge</color> will fill, and when MAXed you gain access to a <color=#ff9900>Hero Skill</color> for <color=#ff9900>5 races</color>! Some Hero Skills can be activated by using Race Items.
63.192: From <color=#ff9900>Bronze 1 to Platinum 4</color>, there are 16 League Ranks. Reaching Platinum 1 bestows a <color=#ff9900>unique title</color> featuring the name of one of your entered Umamusume. Which one can be freely chosen from those who meet the requirements. Battle varied teams on your way to Platinum!
63.193: The teams whose League Score ranks in the top 96 can progress to the Extra Stage! This is composed of 12 races per block, for <color=#ff9900>24 races</color> total. Umamusume entering these races are granted the <color=#ff9900>SUPER HERO</color> epithet! ※Participation can be set in the options
63.194: In the Extra Stage you can cheer for an Umamusume by hitting the <color=#ff9900>"Neighce!"</color> button once per race. Doing so grants you some neighce rewards.
63.195: In each block, the <color=#ff9900>11th race is the Main Race</color>. In A block this will be raced by the top 4 teams, in B block the 5th–8th placed ones. Watching the Main Race grants rewards. All 24 races can also be watched with the focus on 1 Umamusume.
63.196: Through Special Transfer you can <color=#ff9901>obtain gifts for transferring your trained Umamusume to another trainer's team</color>. Be aware you can't get Umamusume back once transferred! Ads are updated <color=#ff9901>every monday at 5:00</color>.
63.197: Each team has its own expectations. These not only come with <color=#ff9901>different rewards</color>, but <color=#ff9901>the higher the expectations, the more luxurious the rewards</color> for transferring your Umamusume to them.
63.198: Teams with high expectations will reward a piece of the transferred <color=#ff9901>Hall of Fame Umamusume</color> as a thank you gift.
63.199: Only Circle Leaders can change the <color=#ff9901>Circle Card</color>. Circle info, comments, and images can be added and customized to show the appeal of your Circle!
63.200: Now you can play the crane game from training whenever you like. Aim for your favourite <color=#ff9900>Umamusume plushies (Paka-Puchi)</color> and view them in your collection! Catch them all and <color=#ff9900>complete the set</color>!
63.201: In this scenario, Umamusume set aside individual goals to pursue a shared dream: winning the <color=#ff9900>Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe</color>! You’ll get <color=#ff9900>one chance in both the Classic and Senior years</color>. Work together with Project L'Arc members to claim victory at the Arc!
63.202: Finishing graded races in the money and SS Matches with L'Arc members gets you <color=#ff9900>Supporter Pt</color> and increases <color=#ff9900>Fan Expectations</color>. Increased Expectations confers stat growth, a training bonus, and facility level ups to lead to further growth for your Umamusume!
63.203: To unleash their true ability on foreign tracks it will be necessary to <color=#ff9900>gain or upgrade Foreign Aptitudes</color>. Obtain Foreign Aptitudes by fulfilling their requirements and level them up to <color=#ff9900>overcome challenges at Foreign Races</color>!
63.204: <color=#ff9900>Interleague friendlies with foreign Umamusume</color> using VR at a virtual Longchamps are held 4 times during training. Like Foreign Races, these races <color=#ff9900>have challenges</color>. Supporter and Aptitude Points can be gained from them, so <color=#ff9900>raise those Foreign Aptitudes</color> and aim for victory!
63.205: You can <color=#ff9900>gain Foreign Aptitudes</color> through SS Matches and winning races. <color=#ff9900>The requirements for each vary</color> so check them out to gain as many as you can!
63.206: The <color=#ff9900>Apt. Pt</color> gained through SS Matches and expeditions abroad can be used to <color=#ff9900>level up Foreign Aptitudes</color>! Leveling them up not only helps you overcome challenges but grants positive effects to aptitudes and bonuses in training. Gather Apt. Pt and level up aggressively!
63.207: L'Arc members fill the <color=#ff9900>Star Gauge</color> through training and races, and <color=#ff9900>once it's full they can join an SS Match</color>! SS Matches will take up a turn, but can be held with <color=#ff9900>up to 5 participants</color>, granting Supporter Pt and stats! You might also find yourself in an even more powerful <color=#ff9900>SSS Match</color> at times.
63.208: When winning an SS Match with L'Arc members, each member will <color=#ff9900>get a winning bonus</color>. Rewards are varied, including Skill Hints and Conditions, so take on the challenge of SS Matches once you get a few members together!
63.209: From early July to early October an <color=#ff9900>Expedition Abroad</color> will have you undergo <color=#ff9900>special training</color> in France. <color=#ff9900>You can gain tons of Apt. Pt</color> while abroad so it is a great chance to level up Foreign Aptitudes!
63.210: During the Expedition Abroad you will enter the <color=#ff9900>Prix Niel</color> and the <color=#ff9900>Prix Foy</color> in early September of the classic and senior years, respectively. These serve as trials for the <color=#ff9900>Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe</color> in early October!
63.211: <color=#ff9900>Once per day</color> you can enter a <color=#ff9900>special race</color> after 10 scout races. These special races don't consume a ticket and are raced against special NPC teams. Winning this race earns you a large amount of Scout Pts.
63.212: In the <color=#ff9901>Derby Stallion: Masters edition of Special Transfers</color> you can transfer your trained Umamusume to another trainer's team for rewards. Be aware that once you transfer someone, she will be gone and you will not be able to get her back.
63.213: Each team has its own expectations. These not only come with <color=#ff9901>different rewards</color>, but <color=#ff9901>the higher the expectations, the more luxurious the rewards</color> for transferring your Umamusume to them. This time, even more luxurious <color=#ff9901>grade 4</color> rewards are available!
63.214: In the <color=#ff9901>Derby Stallion: Masters edition of Special Transfers </color> all transfers will also reward <color=#ff9901>pieces of the transferred Umamusume</color>. Gather a lot of pieces to develop your Umamusume!
63.215: Each race comes in a number of LEVELs. When winning a race, the <color=#ff9901>next LEVEL</color> will unlock.
63.216: You will get a reward the <color=#ff9901>first time you finish first</color> in each LEVEL. Work hard, aim high!
63.217: Each Umamusume in the Hall of Fame can only <color=#ff9901>participate three times</color>.
63.235: Training with Umamusume organized as a <color=#ff9900>Support Card</color> will increase your <color=#ff9900>training efficiency and Friendship Gauge</color>. When the Friendship Gauge is full, <color=#ff9900>Friendship Training</color> can occur. You may <color=#ff9900>gain various benefits</color> if certain others watch you train as well.
63.236: When a Support Card Umamusume has a <color=#ff9900>! mark</color> on her, grab your chance to <color=#ff9900>increase Hint Level of one of this partner's skills</color> upon successfully completing the training session. This will confer a <color=#ff9900>discount on the Skill Pt needed to acquire the skill</color>.
63.237: If you train your Umamusume when her <color=#ff9900>energy is low</color>, she may <color=#ff9900>fail the training</color> and her ability may not improve. There are <color=#ff9900>various disadvantages</color> to failing a training session, so always keep an eye on her <color=#ff9900>energy and failure rate</color>!
63.249: <color=#ff9900>Room Match</color> allows you to race against other trainers with your Hall of Fame Umamusume <color=#ff9900>Host</color>: Set your own conditions for the race <color=#ff9900>Join</color>: Join another trainer's race. <color=#ff9900>Watch</color>: Enter an ID to watch the race.
63.250: The race held will be G1. There are two modes. <color=#ff9900>Simple Mode</color> allows you to hold a race right away. <color=#ff9900>Detailed mode</color> allows you to select weather, participation conditions, etc. first. Up to <color=#ff9900>3 Umamusume per person</color> can be entered.
63.251: Recruit participants for your races from the participation list. Trainers close to you can also be recruited using the <color=#ff9900>Circle and SNS Sharing functions</color>. For future reference, <color=#ff9900>you can save your favorite races</color>. Have a go organizing a race with your friends!
63.252: Save Umamusume in <color=#ff9900>My Entrants</color> to <color=#ff9900>select them easily</color> during registration! You can also save them from the results screen.
63.254: You can check and set your trainer information. On your <color=#ff9900>birthday</color>, you will receive a congratulatory comment from Umamusume on the home screen, and changing your <color=#ff9900>gender</color> will change some scenarios. (Gender can be changed at any time)
63.255: You can set up a <color=#ff9900>representative Umamusume</color> and <color=#ff9900>Support Card</color> to help your followers in their training. You will earn <color=#ff9900>Friend Pt the next day</color> depending on the number of times you do this. (This will be given as a gift)
63.256: You can select the representative Umamusume and Support Card of the friends you <color=#ff9900>follow</color> from each list in training. You also earn more Friend Pt by helping a <color=#ff9900>mutual follower</color> to train. If you don't have many followers, try looking in the <color=#ff9900>recommendations</color>.
63.257: You can check the items you currently have. You can also use consumable items. Some items can be converted to Money. <color=#ff9900>Converting items cannot be undone</color>, so be careful.
63.266: <color=#ff9900>Dream Fest</color> is a new race organized by the legendary Umamusume to reignite excitement in the racing world. Held every year-end, it draws many participants. Train with the legends, grow stronger, and aim to win every race!
63.268: <color=#ff9900>Knowledge</color> is a secret to getting stronger, which you can learn through the guidance of legendary Umamusume. You'll have the opportunity to acquire Knowledge every six turns. Based on the amount in your Guidance Gauge, a few options will be presented, and you will <color=#ff9900>acquire one</color>. Combine them wisely to enhance your training!
63.270: <color=#ff9900>Knowledge</color> is the key to getting stronger, and you can gain it through the guidance of legendary Umamusume. Every six turns, you'll have the chance to acquire Knowledge. Depending on your Guidance Gauge, several options will appear, and you can <color=#ff9900>choose one</color>. Combine them strategically to boost your training!
63.271: <color=#ff9900>Dream Fest</color> is a new race organized by the legendary Umamusume to reignite excitement in the racing world. Held every year-end, it draws many participants. Train with the legends, grow stronger, and aim to win every race!
63.278: Some Knowledge grants powerful effects, but each comes with conditions. You can hold a <color=#ff9900>maximum of 10</color> Knowledge items. After that, you can <color=#ff9900>exchange</color> new Knowledge for ones you already have. Find the best combination to suit the situation!
63.295: You can watch live performances of <color=#ff9900>songs</color> you have acquired. Select main and back dancers from obtained Umamusume and acquired costumes to watch the live with your favorite combination. Songs marked with <color=#ff9900>"Singing"</color>, are voiced by the selected Umamusume. Songs can be acquired through the main story and training.
63.296:
For songs that support the <color=#ff9900>Trainer Camera function</color>, you can <color=#ff9900>control the camera within a certain range</color> during live performances. Choose between two control methods—<color=#ff9900>swipe controls</color> and <color=#ff9900>gyro controls</color>, and enjoy a new kind of live experience!
※Gyro controls are only available on iOS and Google Play versions.
63.297: With <color=#ff9900>swipe controls</color>, you can move the camera by swiping any part of the screen and zoom in by pinching. To return the camera to its default position, select the <color=#ff9900>[Reset Camera]</color> button in the bottom-left corner of the screen.
63.299: You can watch live performances of <color=#ff9900>songs</color> you have acquired. Select main and back dancers from obtained Umamusume and acquired costumes to watch the live with your favorite combination. Songs marked with <color=#ff9900>"Singing"</color>, are voiced by the selected Umamusume. Songs can be acquired through the main story and training.
63.300:
For songs that support the <color=#ff9900>Trainer Camera function</color>, you can <color=#ff9900>control the camera within a certain range</color> during live performances. Choose between two control methods—<color=#ff9900>swipe controls</color> and <color=#ff9900>gyro controls</color>, and enjoy a new kind of live experience!

69.8001: If you're not going fast during the last spurt, you might be lacking speed.
69.8002: If you're losing positions in the final stretch, you might be lacking stamina.
69.8003: If you find yourself unable to get ahead, it might be good to increase your power.
69.8004: If you find yourself unable to catch up in the final stretch, you might be lacking guts.
69.8005: With higher wit, positioning and skill activation becomes easier.
69.8006: If you're low on Money and Support Points, try entering the Daily Races.
69.8007: Upgrading your Support Cards and Umamusume is key to winning races.
69.8008: Race outcomes are not only decided by what happens during the race, but also the weather and sometimes even luck...
69.8009: Upgrading the level of your Support Cards will give you better support effects.
69.8010: Uncapping your Support Cards will give you powerful support effects.
69.8011: The effect [Mood Bonus] also amplifies negative effects, so be careful!
69.8012: The effect [Friendship Bonus] increases the effect of Friendship Training.
69.8013: The [Attribute Bonus] effects increase the results of a specific training.
69.8014: The [Training Bonus] effect increases the results of any training.
69.8015: The [Initial Attribute Bonus] effects increase stats at the start of training.
69.8016: I recommend the [Initial Bond Gauge Bonus] effect if you want to max bond gauges quickly.
69.8017: [Race Bonus] and [Fan Count Bonus] also affect goal races.
69.8018: I recommend the [Race Bonus] effect if you want to earn more Skill Points.
69.8019: The [Hint Level Bonus] effect lets you increase Hint levels more quickly.
69.8020: The [Hint Chance Bonus] effect increases the chance of a Hint showing up.
69.8021: The [Specialty Rate Up] effect increases the chance of a support character appearing on their training type.
69.8022: The [Event Recovery Up] effect increases the energy recovered during events.
69.8023: The [Event Effect Up] effect increases the results of events.
69.8024: The [Failure Rate Down] effect makes it less likely to fail when training with the support character.
69.8025: The [Energy Cost Reduction] effect reduces the energy consumed when training with the support character.
69.8026: The [Wit Training Recovery Up] effect increases the energy recovered when doing Friendship Wit Training.
69.8027: Friendship Trainings will occur after the bond gauge turns orange.
69.8028: When multiple Friendship Trainings occur at once, the effects will be even greater.
69.8029: Events of equipped Support Cards are much more likely to occur.
69.8030: You may sometimes get events from unequipped Support Cards, too!
69.8031: Note: You cannot equip Support Cards of the same Umamusume you are training.
69.8032: You can convert unwanted Support Cards into Horseshoes, which can be exchanged for items in the Shop.
69.8033: You can check the Skill Hints you can get from Support Cards in the [Training Events] section of the details page.
69.8034: You can increase the Awakening level of trainable Umamusume with items and Money.
69.8035: The higher the Awakening level, the more skills you start a training with.
69.8036: You can obtain items for Awakening by winning races of G3 or higher during training.
69.8037: You can upgrade Umamusume by collecting their pieces.
69.8038: Uncapping your Umamusume increases the Level of her unique skills and base stats.
69.8039: Umamusume receive their Race Outfit when uncapped to 3★ or higher.
69.8040: Convert unwanted pieces into clovers, exchangeable for items in the store.
69.8041: Hall of Fame Umamusume can be used in inheritance, Team Stadium, and races.
69.8042: Once a Hall of Fame Umamusume has been transferred, she cannot be recovered.
69.8043: An Umamusume's score in training is calculated from the value of stats and skills.
69.8044: Umamusume entering the Hall of Fame, gain chance and status-based factors.
69.8045: Factors have a rarity, and the more ★s, the more effective.
69.8046: The better you do in training, the easier it is to acquire more factors.
69.8047: Some factors have an effect on the inheritance event at the start of training.
69.8048: When the basic ability factor is activated, the parameter is increased.
69.8049: Aptitude factors increase aptitude for track, distance, or strategy.
69.8050: Skill factors grant you the skill or increase its Hint Level.
69.8051: When the race factor is activated, the parameter and skill Hint Level is increased.
69.8052: Inheritance factors of already acquired skills increase her stats.
69.8053: Parent Umamusume are not lost in inheritance, so use them without fear.
69.8054: You can rent parent Umamusume from your friends for Money.
69.8055: Umamusume compatibility is marked from highest to lowest: ◎ > ○ > △.
69.8056: Class/roommates, family, and such relationships may affect compatibility…
69.8057: Renting a parent Umamusume from a circle member grants a discount.
69.8058: Sometimes, it is useful to refer to the training info of friends' "Main Umamusume".
69.8059: "Rushed" will cause panic and HP loss. Higher wit lowers the chance.
69.8060: Good lane changes ease dodging Umamusume to move forward.
69.8061: Speed is especially important in sprint distance races.
69.8062: Speed and power are especially important in a mile race.
69.8063: In medium-distance races, well-balanced basic abilities are important.
69.8064: Stamina and guts are especially important in long distance races.
69.8065: The marks in the paddock indicate appraisal in the order of ◎>○>▲>△.
69.8066: Going out increases mood and recovers energy.
69.8067: Maybe a trip to the shrine will help you get rid of bad conditions?
69.8068: What happens if you bond with reporter Otonashi after the URA Finals…?
69.8069: It's easier to pass on feelings when the parent Umamusume are a good match.
69.8070: Support Card events can also increase the Hint Lv of rare skills!
69.8071: The school's bulletin board (Home) holds info about Umamusume.
69.8072: Sprint distance means 1400m or less, and mile is from 1401m to 1800m.
69.8073: Medium distance is between 1801m and 2400m, while long distance starts from 2401m.
69.8074: Rain/snow worsen the going: firm > good > soft > heavy, making it difficult to run.
69.8075: The grade of races follows this order: G1 > G2 > G3 > OP > Pre-OP.
69.8076: The higher the grade of the race, the more likely strong Umamusume will gather.
69.8077: G3, G2, and G1 are "big prize" graded races, G1 being the most prestigious.
69.8078: Unique skill factors can be acquired once your Umamusume is 3★ or higher.
69.8079: Courses for the URA Finals are based on which you ran the most during training.
69.8080: Spring Senior Triple Crown: Osaka Hai, Tenno Sho (Spring), Takarazuka Kinen.
69.8081: Triple Tiara is the collective name for: Oka Sho, Oaks, Shuka Sho.
69.8082: Fall Senior Triple Crown: Tenno Sho (Autumn), Japan C, Arima Kinen.
69.8083: Classic Triple Crown: Satsuki Sho, Japanese Derby, Kikuka Sho.
69.8084: If you don't want to skip unread events, you can set this in the options.
69.8085: You can also unlock unobtained Umamusume by using pieces.
69.8086: The growth rate is the ease with which your basic skills increase with training.
69.8087: As Hint Lv increases, Skill Pts needed to acquire skills decreases.
69.8088: You can see opponent's skill activations in PvP, or hide them in options.

88.20070:
— Mom? Hi! It's been a while, how are you? 
— Me? I just finished lunch with Chev and Viv. 
— As usual, Cheval's was all brown and Vivlos 
won't eat anything she doesn't find interesting. 
Really, what am I to do with these two! 
— Oh, but don't worry. I made sure they got their veggies 
and rice. I can get Viv with rewards as always, and Chev… 
I just have to chase her and feed her myself, y'know? 
— Heheh. Aw, it's no problem at all. 
I'm totally used to it. Besides… 
— You know how it is, mama. I love looking after these two.
88.20071:
"—— Her racing heart skips a beat as if responding in joy. 
Right at the final corner's exit, Royce's ears picked up 
the voices of those dear to her with certainty." 

(I can see the image floating in Royce's mind clear as day… 
it tells me this is where I accompany her in pianissimo… 
a vital respite before the climax)  

"«Go for it, Royce!», they shout. 
Hesitation no longer inhabited Royce's heart."  

(Thus we enter the bridge! Just what I was waiting on! 
Playing the main theme in slow tempo! Grandioso!)  

"The sounds of feet digging into the earth. 
A moment later, the packed crowd witnesses 
a streak of light traversing the straight ——"  

"… Perfect! The climax had the ubiquitous strength 
I imagined to it… one of classic youthful passion, 
awakened by the bonds woven up to that point… 
And Earth… you provided the most 
wonderful sonic backdrop to it!"  

"You flatter, the notes stirred my soul 
and I simply had to join in! 
A lovely melody was the natural result. 
It is I who wishes to offer thanks, Ms. Royce!"
88.30172:
"Thank you for joining me at the baseball game today." 
> No problem! It was great fun! 
> (Thanks! sticker) 
"I'm glad you had a good time." 
"I might have behaved a tad immodestly at one point, 
but that was only because the game was just so heated. 
It's not every day that you see a comeback from 6 runs 
behind in the bottom of the 9th inning!" 
"Not that I would know, mind, it's just the gentleman 
in a nearby seat was saying so." 
"That runner's do-or-die base steal to tie the game, 
followed by a safety squeeze were particularly thrilling. 
To are such a play in professional baseball, and have 
the skils to pull it off. Remarkable!" 
> I see, that was really interesting, yeah! 
> (I'm learning! sticker) 
= 5 minutes later… 
"I apologize for the long messages earlier. 
In any case, it was incredibly worthwhile." 
"Should another opportunity arise, we should definitely 
go again. I honestly am not very knowledgeable on 
the topic, but I will accompany you if you wish." 
"[Team Victories da best! sticker]"

88.30174:
Tonight is the "Mejiro's Christmas Night"… 
A special event on a special night, held by the Mejiro 
Umamusume for their unfailingly supportive fans. 
"W-welcome to the Mejiro's Christmas Night! 
Please check in over here!" 
"Huh… you want a picture with me…!? 
…… O-Okay, I can do that……… C-Cheese!" 
That's why Dober, always so tense around others, was 
mustering all her courage to interact with the guests. 
"You're doing great, Dober… Your buccinator is still 
looking tight, but you're welcoming guests magnificently!" 
When I first started secretly looking out for her, I was 
worried she might be having a tough time… but it seems 
that there we no need for me to leave my post…… 
"Oh, what a wonderful night… to be given 
such a present by the Mejiros this year…" 
"… We all put a lot of effort into tonight, hoping that 
everyone would enjoy a wonderful christmas. It would 
make us all very pleased if you came away with some 
great memories." 
Even with ladies she has never met, she manages to 
converse in her own words, without drawing back. 
…… Before long, my zygomaticus major had relaxed 
quite a bit. That's right. Dober had always been like this. 
She always puts a brave step forwards when acting 
for someone, when helping others. 
She's a kind girl like that. 
"… Do your best, Dober!"
88.30175:
"Ms. Ramonu. Lunch has been served. ……Ms. Ramonu?" 
…… No response to my knocking either. 
Fully aware of my ill manner, I opened the door 
to the lounge. Ms. Ramonu was painting. 
It was an image I could not understand —— 
An abstract painting beyond the comprehension of others. 
I had heard about this from another maid. 
There had been a time when Ms. Ramonu's legs were weak, 
and she didn't partake in training during the winter. 
She had spent that time painting abstract images. 
Her fervor, her adulation, her passion, her melancholy —— 
She threw them all at the canvas. Her art, much like herself, 
was imbued with indescribable beauty. 
But why, why has she, at this point, taken up 
her brush once again? 
"… It falls far short of those times. But of course. 
These days, I can come face to face with my love." 
…… My breath was taken away even though I couldn't 
make sense of her words. Without knowing what had 
overcome her, I simply kept gazing at her beauty. 
"The snow has ceased. Let us talk of love.", I heard 
her murmur as I quietly vacated the room. 
…… All that would remain of our meeting was the work 
I hadn't finished, and the white canvas upon which 
she had painted the lushest of greenery.
88.30176:
On a certain day nearing Christmas —— 
"Mmm, it's tough to decide when faced with 
such a large variety of choices～" 
"Indeed… Ryan would likely be happy with 
anything, but… it's always nicer to find something 
that she would truly enjoy, isn't it?" 
"What do you think about horseshoes～? 
My dear sister Ryan patiently accompanied me 
in selecting a pair in the past～" 
"Therefore, I would like to take some time to carefully 
pick out a pair of horseshoes for her this time." 
"I see. So she waited patiently for Bright to decide which 
ones she wanted… Hehe, that's so like Ryan." 
"… I remember, when I was little, she held my hand on 
a stormy night full of thunder. Even though she disliked 
staying up late, she stayed with me the whole night…… 
I always thought I couldn't compare to that." 
"What'd be a good way to repay her… maybe something 
for good sleep? But I'm pretty sure she sleeps well as is…" 
"The store will be closing in 30 minutes. 
We look forward to you next visit." 
"Whoah, it's that time already?!" 
…… Uhhh, What do I do… I'm having a harder 
time picking something than I expected…" 
"That's perfectly fine, Dober. 
You must take your time in expressing gratitude, 
otherwise your feelings might not reach～" 
"…… Heh. Bright could be very right. 
Well, let's come look around more tomorrow then."
88.30177:
Vivlos sets off running. 
The media folk gathered were not done 
asking questions, but quickly realizing 
she could not stand motionless in this moment, 
a wry smile simply formed on their faces. 
Though she must be incredibly tired, the reason 
her steps were light as a feather nonetheless 
could be seen at the end of her gaze.  

"Heey, siiiis～～～! First! 
I came first! I really did it!"  

There was Verxina, meeting her guileless little sister 
running straight at her, no eye for anything else, 
with open arms and an emotional expression.  

"Vivlos… thank you…! 
You ran an incredible, fantastic final leg. 
Those 7cm I couldn't close… 
The things I couldn't see behind them… 
You revealed them to me today."  

"Ehehe～ I have a second stomach for compliments～～♪"  

"… While I still thought of you as my cute, 
needy little sister, somewhere along you've 
become so strong."  

"Well my older sister's well known for her spirit, 
so of course I'll win if I set my thoughts on it! 
Ah, but even so, I'll always be a cute little sister♡"  

"Hahahah, I guess so. I'd love to see you 
being cute and strong out there."  

"Yeah! I'm gonna go win a lot! 
In huge races, or against powerful opponents! 
And I'll always come back for your compliments♪ 
What do you think? Deal?♡"
88.30178:
"Duramente drifts far to the outside! 
A mistake likely to cost her dear!!" 
 
I can hear the roars of the crowd between 
that of the wind rushing past my ears. 
I feel removed from my body, like it is not my own. 
 
(Have I lost my composure...?!) 
 
No, it's not that. It's not nerves sending shivers 
through me, but something deep inside, an urge —— 
 
"Haaaaaaaaaaah!!" 
 
"Duramente from the outside! Can you believe it, 
Duramente has found a way from the outside!!" 
 
That's right... it's the urge in my blood, the pride 
within its line. It stimulates me, encouraging, 
emboldening, to prove that I am the "strongest". 
 
"Is this what she is capable of!? Duramente!!"
88.30179:
Hanachōzu; floating flowers in a Shinto ablution basin. 
Spectacular colors adorning a new year still far 
from springtime's blossoming buds. 
Both of us momentarily taken by their beauty. 
Our wishes are like buds waiting to open — those were 
the words softly leaving your lips. To let them bloom. 
 
For each of the numerous flowers laying within 
the basin, so too a wish lay within me. 
Plip-plop, plip-plop. One by one, droplets fell 
underneath this branch of the Satono tree, 
drawing expanding rings upon the water's surface. 
I am reminded of drops from days past, drops which 
followed the curves of my cheeks. 
The pile of unflowering flowers. 
 
I'll let them blossom this time, on the most 
floriferous once in a lifetime stage. 
I'll let these flowers — these wishes — reach full bloom, 
like this beautiful hanachōzu. 
 
"Yeah. We'll have them blooming, without fail." 
You nodded your head, with a smile as warm as 
the sunlight stretching over the buds.
88.30180:
Umamusume — taking on names of another world, 
succeeding their corresponding spirit and accompanying 
histories, both brilliant and tragic, they are born to run. 
Through their many races, these girls eventually 
become part of history themselves. 
 
"I'll be Japan's number one Umamusume!" 
A vow made to her two mothers. Harboring her 
ambition to be "Japan's number one", a girl leaving behind 
her hometown encounters rivals, competes with them 
in races, and through her victories and defeats eventually 
turns that dream of hers into reality. 
 
"I'll win regardless." 
A "sovereign" chasing after the "emperor". 
Spurred by an unyielding spirit, she fought through 
repeated setbacks to accomplish miracles in front of 
the friends who always ran by her side and the rival 
who supported her all the way. 
 
"Everyone said they want to see me run..." 
A young girl in awe of the unbreakable "sovereign". 
Together with her bosom friend with whom she exchanged 
a promise, she jumped into the world of racing. 
Though beset by doubt in her own dream, she managed 
to find herself, becoming a festival girl beloved by all. 
 
All said —— 
"Ah, over here, Spe!" 
"Wooh, I made it~! My battle meal was 
more delicious than I anticipated..." 
"Geez~ The race is about to start! 
—— Ah, I know! Why don't we race to the paddock? 
We can establish which one of us is number one♪" 
"Oh, that sounds fun! Wanna have a go at it, Spe?" 
"Of course! I might have arrived last, 
but I'm gonna finish first~!" 
"Okaay, get ready... go!!" 
The road they travel has not yet reached its end.
