Aoharu Hai
Shine On, Team Bonds
119.3:
Connect, Shine, Sparkle
Our Grand Concert
119.4:
Make a new track!!
Climax Overture
119.6:
Reach for the stars
Project L'Arc
119.9:
Run! Mecha Umamusume
Invention of Dreams
119.11:
Welcome to the Deserted Island
Design Your Island

120.1: The eccentric young director, Akikawa, has launched a brand-new tournament: the <color=#FF6D26>URA Finals</color>! Now, trainer-and-Umamusume duos will battle it out to claim the title of inaugural champions!
120.2:
Teamwork! A new chapter of youth!
The <color=#FF6D26>Aoharu Hai</color> tournament begins!
But there's no time to enjoy it―the academy faces a sudden crisis! To keep Tracen's freedom, they must unite, fight, and claim victory!
120.3: Why do Umamusume perform live? Through the mysterious producer's <color=#FF6D26>Grand Live</color> plan, each Umamusume must face her own reasons for performing. What truths will they uncover along the way?
120.4: The media has launched a brand-new tournament: the <color=#FF6D26>Twinkle Star Climax</color>! A fierce showdown to determine the very strongest. Run freely, chase your dreams, and aim for the top!
120.5: Just as trainers dedicate themselves to their Umamusume, a new force emerges: a support AI carrying the wisdom of the Three Goddesses. Armed with this guidance, they must now take on the ultimate challenge ― the <color=#FF6D26>Grand Masters</color>!
120.6: The Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe ― racing's ultimate prize. For those who refuse to stop striving, this is the year to reach the very top. At Tracen Academy, <color=#FF6D26>Project L'Arc</color> begins ― an ambitious journey driven by passion, dreams, and destiny.
120.7: The <color=#FF6D26>U.A.F.</color> ― the ultimate all-around tournament to crown the No.1 Umamusume athlete ― is here! In 15 unique events, these competitors will push past their limits and scatter sweat in battle. Open your eyes wide and witness their fighting spirit ignite!
120.8:
With Director Akikawa's big announcement, the great farming era has begun at Tracen Academy! Under the bright sun they work the fields side by side, and when dusk falls, they gather to share a hearty meal.
All right ― back to the fields today!
120.9: A Mecha-Umamusume has appeared at Tracen Academy! Created by the genius inventor Sugar Lights, it's still an early prototype ― but we'll tune it up and make the doctor's dream a reality!
120.10: When the Twinkle Series faces a crisis, a group of “legendary” Umamusume rises to the challenge! Now, everyone in the racing world must come together to revive the series and carry it boldly into the future!
120.11: The deserted island project is underway! Born from Tucker Bryne's dream, it's time to let instincts run wild! Burn bright, Umamusume! Push your body and mind to the limit ― build the ultimate training facility!

163.1001: My name is Special Week! My dream is to be the best Umamusume in Japan! I'm gonna pull my own weight to make my moms proud!
163.1002: I'm Silence Suzuka. I like to run. I'm not giving the lead to anyone. Um... That's all.
163.1003: Heya, I'm Tokai Teio! I'm going to be an undefeated Triple Crown Umamusume, so don't let me out of your sight!
163.1004: Hi, I'm Maruzensky! Did you come to see this new style of running too? Hehe ♪ Even though I'm crazy about it... I don't know how to feel ♪
163.1005: I'm the jet-black entertainer, Fuji Kiseki! I'll make you smile with my best "miracle"!
163.1006: I am Oguri Cap. I'm going to do my best to make everyone in my hometown happy. Please take care of me.
163.1007: Yo, I'm Gold Ship! I don't care if it's on the turf, on fire, or at the edge of the universe. I'm going to find something interesting wherever I can! ☆
163.1008: Yo, I'm Vodka! My goal is to be the coolest Umamusume in the world! I'm not gonna do anything stupid. Remember that!
163.1009: Hello, I'm Daiwa Scarlet! I'll do my best to... Hmph! I'm going to be number one. That's all!
163.1010: Howdy! I'm Taiki Shuttle! I'm here to make everyone happy with my powerful running!
163.1011: My name is Grass Wonder. Since I was born as a Umamusume, I want to pursue this path to the end. Hehe ♪
163.1012: There are a lot of good-lookin' people here... hehe. I'll take them all on. I'm Hishiama! Come on, let's get to it!
163.1013: My name is Mejiro McQueen. Conquering the "Spring Tennosho" has been a long-cherished goal of the Mejiro family, and I will do it with my own two legs.
163.1014: I'm the crimson bird that runs the course! El Condor Pasa is closing in! I'm flying around the world!
163.1015: Haa-ha-ha-ha! I am the strongest and most beautiful of them all, the "Supreme King", T.M. Opera O! Now, let the legend begin!
163.1016: ...I'm Narita Brian. I don't have a story to tell you. I just run, crush, and win.
163.1017: I am Symboli Rudolf. I am the one who will stand at the top of every Umamusume and lead them to become "Emperors". Those of you who share my aspirations, let's work together to conquer the world!
163.1018: I am Air Groove. If you don't bend your beliefs, your ideals will surely sprout. To demonstrate this, I, the Empress, will be the guiding light for everyone.
163.1019: Hewwo! I'm Digi-tan! I'm a massive fan of all of the sparkling Umamusume! I'm so happy every day! I'm so glad I was born an otaku!~♪
163.1020: Yahoo-, it's Seiun Sky. Take your time and relax... When you're aiming for a big goal, it's important to take your time, right?
163.1021: Ah'm Tamamo Cross! A'hm gonna win'n win'n win to make a name for myself! Don't underestimate me just 'cause ah'm small!
163.1022: Good day, I'm Fine Motion! I want to make lots of great memories. First things first, I want to know where the best noodle shops are. ♪
163.1023: I'm Biwa Hayahide. My goal is to assemble the perfect winning formula. ...Also, I have a normal-sized head!
163.1024: Ehehe, I'm Mayachin!☆ I love thrilling and exciting things~ Nice to meetcha!
163.1025: ...I am Manhattan Cafe. I have a friend I want to catch up to... The girl who always runs in front of me... She's right there...
163.1026: My name is Mihono Bourbon. My goal is locked onto becoming a Triple Crown Umamusume. Please refer to my data for legwork and other information.
163.1027: My name is Mejiro Ryan! Train your body, stay healthy! Grow some muscle, stay fit! Let's go for it!
163.1028: I'm Hishi Akebono ♪ I'll put lo~ts of love into both cooking and running for everybody! It's nice to meet you!~
163.1029: Oh, my name is Yukino Bijin! My dream is to become a stylish city gal in the Twankle Series! Phew... I hope I said that right...
163.1030: I'm... Rice Shower. Um... I'm a useless girl who makes others unhappy... but I'm trying my best to change!
163.1031: Hey hey~! I'm Ines Fujin! I'm going to race and work hard to make sure my family is happy!~
163.1032: Aren't you interested about how fast a Umamusume can go? If you are, I, Agnes Tachyon, would like you to be my guinea pig.
163.1033: Admire Vega. ...Can I go now? I need to train more, win more races, and I need to become a first-magnitude star.
163.1034: The hell are ya sayin'?! I'm Inari One! As you can see, I'm an efficient child of Edo! I wanna become the biggest Umamusume of them all!
163.1035: My... My... My dream is to be a Derby Umamusume! And then there's... ah! My name!!!! My name is Winning Ticket! Nice to meet you!
163.1036: I'm Air Shakur. In any case, data speaks louder than victory or defeat. I don't have a problem with simulation, I'll screw you over, logistically.
163.1037: My name is Eishin Flash. In order to keep the tradition of Umamusume alive, I will continue to run. Every race and everything else is on schedule.
163.1038: I'm Curren, a.k.a. Curren Chan! I'm going to wrap the world in "cuteness"!☆ Don't look away, look at Curren ♪
163.1039: Oh-ho-ho! I am Kawakami Princess... Yes, a princess above all princesses! I'll daintily knock you off of your feet at the races!
163.1040: Gold City. ...Just so you know, I won't forgive you if you treat me like a doll. Don't judge me by my looks, but by the way I run.
163.1041: Hello! My name is Sakura Bakushin O! As you can see, I am a brilliant class representative! Let's set a great example for everyone! BAKUSHIIIN!
163.1042: Haa-ha-ha-ha! It's Seeking the Pearl! Guess what? The world is full of possibilities, and I'm gonna prove it to you!
163.1043: Roar~! It's Shinko Windy! You scared? You can tell me if you're scared~! ...Hey! Don't ignore me! Grrrrr!
163.1044: Sweep Tosho is my pre-transformation name! I am Sweepy the Magical Girl! Now this is sorcery! Aaah!! (Bonk)
163.1045: Tee-hee... I'm Super Creek~ I'll do my best to make everyone smile. Please leave it to me ♪
163.1046: I'm Smart Falcon! You can call me Falco! My dream is to become a Umadol! Autographs are always welcome ☆
163.1047: My name is Zenno Rob Roy. Well... this is me, but I'm longing for a heroic tale... I would like to tell my story within a race someday...!
163.1048: I'm Tosen Jordan. My dream is... actually, serious topics are NG~☆ Anyways, look at my nails! Aren't they cool?
163.1049: It's Nakayama Festa. Halfhearted races don't give me a thrill. Hey... Let me feel the intense heat of the race...!
163.1050: Narita Taishin. That's all. I just want to win and shove it in the faces of the ones who made fun of me... Leave me alone.
163.1051: Hello, my name is Nishino Flower. I want to become a nice, sisterly Umamusume so that everyone can rely on me...!
163.1052: I'm Haru Urara! I love carrots and I lo~ve running because it's fun!♪ I'm going to try my very best to finish first!
163.1053: Hey there! Bamboo Memory! I'm going to run hard to earn the name of "Demon Director of the Public Discipline Committee"!
163.1054: The hero of justice, Biko Pegasus, is here! I can take down any formidable foe and make everyone smile! Isn't that great!
163.1055: Hi hi~, I'm Marvelous Sunday! I'm bringing a Marvelous feeling to the whole world! Now, let's all be Marvelous together!
163.1056: Hello! They call me Matikanefukukitaru! I believe in the divine messages of Shiraoki-sama, and I constantly am working on my fortune telling, waiting for the day I'll be blessed with good fortune!
163.1057: There's a breeze only racing can offer. It's light, clear, and..... an unrestrained tailwind. --I'm Mr. C.B.. Nice to meet you.
163.1058: I-I'm Me-Meisho Doto! U-uhm, uhm... I've been trying my best to become more confident in... m-mythelf- OWW!
163.1059: Hello... I'm Mejiro Dober. I'm a Umamusume of the Mejiro family, and I'm not ashamed to say that... I intend to do my best.
163.1060: Uh... I'm Nice Nature. I guess I don't really live up to the name of "Nice Nature", haha... Let's take it easy, shall we?
163.1061: Ohhh-ho-ho! My name is King Halo. As a first-class Umamusume, I'll give you the best results... And show the world this talent of mine!
163.1062: Yoo-hoo, I'm Matikanetannhauser. I've been practicing hard so I won't lose to anyon—Oh, today's my day off?!
163.1063: My name is Ikuno Dictus. If you are looking for management, leave it to me. I will manage you thoroughly with an iron will.
163.1064: I'm Mejiro Palmer! How ya doing~? Well, if you ever need anything, I'm always here. Feel free to talk to me ♪
163.1065: Weee~iii! I'm Daitaku Helios~! I'm gonna run the most hype race ever, so please give me your best call! ☆
163.1066: Twin Turbo! I'll take the first Turbo, I'll take it for sure! Let's go, Turbo, full throttle!!!
163.1067: My name is Satono Diamond. My fate has never been decided from the beginning. I will make the future shine with my running!
163.1068: I'm Kitasan Black! I'm going to run as fast as I can to make this race as exciting as a festival!
163.1069: I'm S-Sakura Chiyono O! I will make my dream of standing on my ideal stage with the person of my dreams blossom!
163.1070: Sirius Symboli! No need to talk about the race. Just shut up and watch. I'm going to conquer the world and prove that I'm the strongest.
163.1071: My name is Mejiro Ardan. I want to run proudly, even if these legs will be short-lived... Even if only for a moment, I would like to shine in a race.
163.1072: I'm Yaeno Muteki. As a disciple of the Kongo Yaegaki way, I desire to race with the strong. Come on, let's fight like crazy!!
163.1073: Tsurumaru Tsuyoshi! Aiming to become the "Triple Crown Umamusume" of my dreams! I'll give it my all... BLEH! I-I just swallowed a lot of blood! I'm fine, I'm alright!
163.1074: ............Hmm? Is it time for me to introduce myself? Heheheh, my name is Mejiro Bright. I will try my best as a member of the Mejiro family~.
163.1076: I'm Sakura Laurel. My goal is the world. The Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe! --Well, it's just a "dream" now, but... I'll make it come true someday for sure!
163.1077: Hello, I'm Narita Top Road! I will do my best to live up to the expectations of all of the ones who support me!

169.1048: Her parents always told her to eat her veggies first. That always made her the most upset.
169.1049: All of her family members are poor sleepers.
169.1050: Rumor has it that the moms of BNW are friends now.
169.1051: Her most treasured item is a watering can given to her by her parents.
169.1052: Her favorite dish is her mother's carrot rice.
169.1053: Her father, a passionate gym teacher, is her mentor and origin point.
169.1054: Sunday mornings are Tokusatsu time with the whole family!
169.1055: She loves her grandma, and they go leaf peeping together in the fall.
169.1056: Like an excellent older sister, she admires her younger sister's cheerfulness.
169.1058: She is proficient in many languages due to her family's frequent relocation.
169.1059: Her father is sad that he can no longer call her "Ber-chan".
169.1060: Her parents' snack bar is decorated with articles about their daughter.
169.1061: Her mother is catastrophically incapable of housework, so she has servants.
169.1062: Whenever she goes home, her parents hang a banner at their restaurant.
169.1063: She tends to lead family meetings.
169.1064: Her father is a master golfer, but their scores have been reversed.
169.1065: Playing dead always fools her parents lol
169.1066: Her parents found their frail daughter's recklessness to be an indication of growth.
169.1067: Her father is a distinguished man and a philanthropist in the Umamusume world.
169.1068: A family of 30 people, including her father's disciples, live with her.
169.1069: Dinner was often a potluck with her family.
169.1070: Her father used to hire a different private tutor every day.
169.1071: My mother wants me to invite my friends from the academy over to our house.
169.1072: Whenever she returns home, she always pats her grandfather on the shoulder.
169.1074: During homecoming season, her whole family comes to pick her up.
169.1076: Her father passed down his recipe for omelettes and galettes to her.
169.1077: She gets her angry eyes from her father.
169.1078: Her home is famous in her hometown for being a fancy house where fairies live.
169.1079: Their staple on birthdays is a tart with Asian pears.
169.1080: She tries to avoid her parents on social media.
169.1082: She often chats with her older sister at family meet-ups.
169.1083: The whole family drinks their coffee black in the mornings.
169.1084: Their house's nameplate is made of a broken fence. (Made by her mother.)
169.1085: A photograph of her mother and grandmother hangs in her room.
169.1086: The wintersweet in their garden is a family favorite.
169.1087: When her mother fell asleep on the couch, she was in charge of carrying her to bed.
169.1088: They share their random thoughts through social media.
169.1089: Family members take turns deciding the destinations of their overseas trips.
169.1090: Often has serious talks during catch ball.
169.1091: Their father's hamburg steaks are a staple at family gatherings.
169.1093: Her vocabulary increases slightly when she talks to her parents.
169.1094: She can't get over the fact that her older brother is popular with the girls.
169.1096: Her father cheers for his daughter's race at home using a war drum.
169.1097: She and her father often discuss history together.
169.1098: She has a lot of siblings, so her home is very lively ☆
169.1099: Her allowance always includes some fine Tomakomai sweets.
169.1100: Her mother is the most relaxed person in her family.
169.1102: They tend to chat through jam sessions.
169.1104: Her parents say that she's aughty and a handful to this day.
169.1105: She can understand about 54% of what her dad says.
169.1106: Her parents sent in her application to the academy before she could.
169.1107: She boasts the flavor of her mother's baked marshmallow pie.
169.1108: Her family gets serious in table tennis matches at hot spring vacations.
169.1109: They often go picnicking when they're together.
169.1110: Her mother has a secret recipe for carrot glacé.
169.1111: They all write in their own diaries.
169.1115: She inherited her artistic sense from her parents.
169.1116: She's been taken up Mt. Fuji to the third station at 3 years old, the 5th station at 5 and to the top at 7.
169.1117: Her mother taught her nail care.
169.1119: Not a day goes by that she doesn't think about them.
169.1120: She can tell what her parents are thinking about from their facial expressions alone.
169.1121: Who gets to do house chores is decided through games of "Acchi Muite Hoi".
169.1124: They all have a refined sweet smell.

228.99:
Now, it's music time～♪ 
Which song is Trainer-san's favorite～?
228.149:
Hm, hmm, hm～ hnn～…
Oh my, am I too slow～?
228.150: Here we go～! When Falcon runs～? One, two… "We run after her!" Ehe♪ Thanks everyone☆
228.151: Wah～ They're all great songs! Tell me your favorite, trainer♪
228.152: Eyy don't run off, listen! The waves'll leave a Golshi shaped impression on your eardrums…☆
228.153: This tone reverberates in my heart. What sort of tracks do you prefer, Trainer?
228.154:
Music keeps me running! 
What songs do you like to run to?
228.155:
Oho, what a great selection of tracks 
I see you have great taste～!
228.156: Put on something energetic to dance to!
228.157: Huh, I like this track! The sounds are filling my head with amazing magics!
228.158: Music? …I don't hate it. Lets me shut out the noise.
228.159:
Hearing these songs reminds 
me of my rivals!
228.174:
Songs that bring luck change 
with time! Isn't that interesting?
228.175:
Now that's a spiffy tune…! 
I can't wait ta be a "city girl" 
befitting of them vibes～…!
228.176:
What a very, very nice song～! 
What dance would fit it?
228.183:
DJ Heli in da house! 
Put your hands up, it's party time!
228.184:
Gotta go fast, WEEEII! 
I wanna have a blast singing 
my lungs out with Milady again～♪
228.187:
This sound is special to me. Like a gust 
of wind rushing through my heart, leaving 
its lingering scent... I cherish it.

<size=27>The snow in my hometown was quiet and pure, 
and it was white as far as eyes could see. 
It's truly one of my most precious and nostalgic sceneries. 
I wanted to be able to express how I feel about it… to you. 
I want to keep running alongside you to the end of this landscape. 
</size>

385.904601: Raise mood <color=#ff911c>3 times</color> to enter <color=#ff911c>SUPER</color> mood for 3 turns.
385.904602: Upon entering a SUPER state, you will no longer get migraines.
385.904603: While in a SUPER state, your <color=#ff911c>mood will not drop</color>.
385.904604:
While in a SUPER mood, the bonus for training effects from
mood becomes <color=#ff911c>55%</color>.
385.904605:
When you raise the mood while in a SUPER state, the effect's
duration is extended by <color=#ff911c>1 turn</color> (max 2 times).
385.904606: When the SUPER state ends, your mood becomes Great.
385.904701: Succeed at training <color=#ff911c>4 times</color> to enter the <color=#ff911c>Challenge Zone</color>.
385.904702: While in the Challenge Zone, you will not get lazy.
385.904703:
While in the Challenge Zone, training <color=#ff911c>won't fail</color>, its effects get
<color=#ff911c>+30%</color> bonus and energy consumption reduced by <color=#ff911c>50%</color>.
385.904704:
After each training, the Challenge Zone may end based on an end
rate affected by <color=#ff911c>turn count</color> and <color=#ff911c>remaining health</color>. It also ends
automatically after a set number of turns.
385.904705: The Challenge Zone will end if you <color=#ff911c>rest or go on outings</color>.
385.904706:
When the Challenge Zone ends, you <color=#ff911c>gain parameters</color> based on
its duration. The acquired parameters will change depending
on how it ends.
385.904801: New <color=#ff911c>Training Partners</color> with their specialty will join you.
385.904802: Umamusume with a specialty gain a <color=#ff911c>Bestie Gauge</color> and <color=#ff911c>Bestie Lv</color>.
385.904803:
While the Bestie Gauge is <color=#ff911c>MAX</color>, the partner will be placed in their
<color=#ff911c>specialty training</color>.
385.904804:
When the Bestie Gauge is <color=#ff911c>MAX</color>, the partner will trigger
<color=#ff911c>Friendship Training</color>.
385.904805:
The Bestie Gauge increases from gaining Bond during training
and events.
385.904806:
When you do Friendship Training with a partner while the
Bestie Gauge is MAX, the <color=#ff911c>Bestie Gauge resets</color>, and
<color=#ff911c>Bestie Lv increases</color>.
385.904807:
Umamusume with a specialty have an additional <color=#ff911c>bonus effect</color>
on training based on their Bestie Lv.
